My meme

Here my beautiful Walt meme comes from my favourite show Breaking Bad. As we all dont like copy cats i have referenced Saul goodman suggesting that the theif should lawyer up.

library(magick)

#Walter white
walt <- image_read(path = 'https://cdn.pastemagazine.com/www/articles/BREAKING-BAD-main.jpg') %>% 
  image_scale(500)


#Square one
top_square <- image_blank(width=500,
                            height=100,
                            color = '#000000') %>% 
  image_annotate(text = "When people take 'inspiration'\n from my work",
                 color = "#999999",
                 size = 30,
                 font = 'Impact',
                 gravity = 'north')
                              

#Square two
bottom_square <- image_blank(width=500,
                             height = 150,
                             color = '#000000') %>% 
  image_annotate(text = 'You Better call Saul',
                 color = '#999999',
                 size = 40,
                 font = "calibri",
                 gravity = 'center')



merge_meme <- c(top_square, walt,bottom_square)



#Putting it all togethor
finished_meme <- image_append(merge_meme, stack =TRUE)

#saving the meme file
image_write(finished_meme,'my_meme.png')

My animated GIF

Growing up I always watched Pokemon in the mornings and has become a fond childhood memory of mine. Here the GIF is the first introduction between Ash and Pikachu which is a representation of me meeting programming for first time. 

library(magick)

#First Frame
frame1 <- image_read('Pika1.jpg') %>% 
  image_scale(500)

#Second Frame
frame2 <- image_read('Pika2.jpg') %>% 
  image_scale(500)

#Third frame
frame3 <- image_read('Pika3.jpg') %>% 
  image_scale(500)

#4th Frame
frame4 <- image_read('Pika4.jpg') %>% 
  image_scale(500)

Pikas <- c(frame1,frame2,frame3,frame4)

animation <- image_animate(Pikas, fps=1)

#Saving as gif
image_write(animation, 'my_animation.gif')
